![Sam.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1614779503564-WAR7F6JSKQMH5KZ7RV2V/Sam.jpg)

Sam Wilson just can't catch a break. Ever since he took on the mantle of Captain America (which was bestowed upon him by the original Steve Rogers) he has become a political lightning rod, inadvertently inciting divisiveness wherever the hero goes. In this retrospective, we take a deep look at Nick Spencer's take on the Sentinel of Liberty and why Sam's turn with the shield was met with so much controversy.**  
  
